      • stringToEnumWeightMap

        public static <T extends Enum<T>> Map<T,Double> stringToEnumWeightMap(String s,
                                                      Class<T> type)
        Convert a string of the form [ENUM_1 : 0.8, ENUM_2 : 0.2] to a Map<Enum, Double>. The returned map is immutable.
        Parameters:
        s - the string to parse
        type - Class to use as the key of the returned map
        Returns:
        a new immutable Map<Enum, Double> of identifiers and weights
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if supplied string is malformed or empty, or if weights do not sum to 1.0, within DataUtils.WEIGHT_TOLERANCE
        NumberFormatException - if supplied string does not contain parseable double values

      • stringToValueValueWeightMap

        public static NavigableMap<Double,Map<Double,Double>> stringToValueValueWeightMap(String s)
        Convert a string of the form [6.5 :: [1.0 : 0.8, 5.0 : 0.2]; 10.0 :: [1.0 : 0.2, 5.0 : 0.8]] to a NavigableMap<Double, Map<Double, Double>. The returned map and nested maps are immutable and should only be accessed via Map.entrySet() references or using keys derived from Map.keySet() as Double comparisons are inherently problematic.
        Parameters:
        s - the string to parse
        Returns:
        a new immutable Map<Double, Double> of values and their weights
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if s is malformed or empty, or if weights do not sum to 1.0, within DataUtils.WEIGHT_TOLERANCE
        NumberFormatException - if s does not contain parseable double values

      • stringToValueWeightMap

        public static NavigableMap<Double,Double> stringToValueWeightMap(String s)
        Convert a string of the form [1.0 : 0.4, 2.0 : 0.6] to a NavigableMap<Double, Double>. The returned map is immutable and should only be accessed via Map.entrySet() references or using keys derived from Map.keySet() as Double comparisons are inherently problematic.
        Parameters:
        s - the string to parse
        Returns:
        a new immutable Map<Double, Double> of values and their weights
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if s is malformed or if weights do not sum to 1.0, within DataUtils.WEIGHT_TOLERANCE
        NumberFormatException - if s does not contain parseable double values

      • intListToRangeString

        public static String intListToRangeString(List<Integer> values)
        Convert an ordered list of non-repeating Integers to a compact string form. For example, List<Integer>.toString() = "[1, 2, 3, 4, 10, 19, 18, 17, 16]" would instead be written as "[[1:4],10,[19:16]]".
        Parameters:
        values - the values to convert
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if values is empty or if values contains adjacent repeating values
        See Also:
        rangeStringToIntList(String)

      • rangeStringToIntList

        public static List<Integer> rangeStringToIntList(String s)
        Complement of intListToRangeString(java.util.List<java.lang.Integer>) converts a string of the form "[[1:4],10,[19:16]]" to an ordered List<Integer> (e.g. [1, 2, 3, 4, 10, 19, 18, 17, 16]). This method should only be called with strings created by intListToRangeString(java.util.List<java.lang.Integer>), otherwise results are undefined.
        Parameters:
        s - the string to convert
        See Also:
        intListToRangeString(java.util.List<java.lang.Integer>)

      • stripZeros

        public static String stripZeros(String s)
        Strip trailing zeros of a decimal number that has already been formatted as a string. Method will leave a single zero after a decimal. Method will not alter exponential forms, which may have a critical '0' in last position.
        Parameters:
        s - the string to clean

      • trimEnds

        public static String trimEnds(String s)

        s - String to trim
        Throws:
